question.value:
A systematic review and meta analysis will be carried out to address the main question. Data will be extracted according to the PRISMA guidelines. The screening process to be used in the search will involve a hierarchy of assessments that begin by identifying relevant journal titles (with duplicates removed), followed by the abstract and full article review.  

Final decision on the eligibility of the article will be based on the inclusion and exclusion criteria. Relevant articles will be identified by electronic searches of Scopus, Pubmed, Web of Science, EMBASE, CINAHL, Cochrane Library, Medline and ProQuest databases from January 2012 to April 2020. The text words “irisin” or “FNDC5” will be combined using AND with the text words “weight training” OR “resistance training” OR “resistance exercise” OR “strength training” OR “strength exercise” in all databases. 

Inclusion criteria 
1.	Design:  Randomised controlled trials and comparison studies.
2.	Population: Men and/or women aged 18 years and older.
3.	Intervention:  Resistance training (specifying type, intensity, repetition maximum, frequency, and session duration), for any intervention duration, including pre- and post-acute studies.
4.	Comparison: Aerobic training (specifying type, intensity, frequency, and session duration), for any intervention duration, including pre- and post-acute studies.
5.	Outcome: Chronic and/or acute peripheral irisin levels.

Exclusion criteria 
1.	non-intervention studies;
2.	theoretical articles or descriptions of treatment approaches; 
3.	review articles; 
4.	unpublished studies, abstracts or dissertations; 
5.	articles with-out adequate specification of interventions, and/or comparisons; 
6.	non-peer reviewed articles and book chapters;
7.	animal studies.
8.	non-English language articles;

